HEADWORD: Catelectrotonus
<hw>Cat`e*lec*trot"o*nus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <?/ down + <?/ (see <er>Electro-</er>) + <?/ tone.]</ety>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>The condition of increased irritability of a
nerve in the region of the cathode or negative electrode, on the passage
of a current of electricity through it.</def>⟦br⟧
